            <title>Wikimedia Commons picture of the day for June 24</title>
            <link>https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FeedItem/potd/20260624000000/en</link>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FeedItem/potd/20260624000000/en</guid>
            <description>&lt;div class=&quot;mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output&quot; lang=&quot;en&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;table class=&quot;toccolours floatright&quot; style=&quot;width:300px;text-align:center&quot;&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;th lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Commons:Picture_of_the_day&quot; title=&quot;Commons:Picture of the day&quot;&gt;Picture of the day&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/th&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class=&quot;toccolours&quot; style=&quot;padding:0&quot;&gt;&lt;span typeof=&quot;mw:File&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/File:Messier_24_(infrared,_red,_green).jpg&quot; class=&quot;mw-file-description&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/25/Messier_24_%28infrared%2C_red%2C_green%29.jpg/330px-Messier_24_%28infrared%2C_red%2C_green%29.jpg&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;113&quot; class=&quot;mw-file-element&quot; srcset=&quot;https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/25/Messier_24_%28infrared%2C_red%2C_green%29.jpg/960px-Messier_24_%28infrared%2C_red%2C_green%29.jpg 2x&quot; data-file-width=&quot;7680&quot; data-file-height=&quot;2880&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;div lang=&quot;en&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot; class=&quot;description en&quot; style=&quot;display:inline;&quot;&gt;The &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Small_Sagittarius_Star_Cloud&quot; class=&quot;extiw&quot; title=&quot;en:Small Sagittarius Star Cloud&quot;&gt;Small Sagittarius Star Cloud (Messier 24)&lt;/a&gt; is a dust-free window into distant regions of the &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Milky_Way&quot; class=&quot;extiw&quot; title=&quot;en:Milky Way&quot;&gt;Milky Way&lt;/a&gt;, visible to the naked eye in dark skies. This 3-panel mosaic spans only a small portion of the star cloud in near infrared and visible light. The field includes the open clusters &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NGC_6603&quot; class=&quot;extiw&quot; title=&quot;en:NGC 6603&quot;&gt; NGC 6603&lt;/a&gt; (left) and Collinder 469 (center), the dark nebula &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barnard_92&quot; class=&quot;extiw&quot; title=&quot;en:Barnard 92&quot;&gt; Barnard 92&lt;/a&gt; (right), and the H-II region &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sh_2-41&quot; class=&quot;extiw&quot; title=&quot;en:Sh 2-41&quot;&gt;Sharpless 41&lt;/a&gt; (green glow). Tonight, the Small Sagittarius Star Cloud can be seen all night from most of the world.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
            <pubDate>Wed, 24 Jun 2026 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
